==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: field mouse
<hw>field mouse</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>any nocturnal Old World mouse of the
genus <gen>Apodemus</gen> inhabing woods and fields and
gardens.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>any mouse inhabiting fields, as
the <stype>campagnol</stype> and the <stype>deer mouse</stype>. See
<er>Campagnol</er>, and <er>Deer mouse</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fieldpiece</ent>⟦br⟧
